    <!--
    =====================================================================
    LINE 2: LINEARLAYOUT START + NAMESPACE DECLARATION
    =====================================================================
    <LinearLayout
        xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"

    EXPLANATION:
    - <LinearLayout> → Ek container start kar rahe hain jo cheezo ko
                       line mein rakhta hai (jaise ek dibba)
    - xmlns:android → "XML Namespace" - android ki properties kahan se
                       laani hai ye batata hai
    - "http://..." → Android ka official URL jahan sab properties defined hain

    DRYRUN: Jab Android ye line dekhega:
            1. Ek LinearLayout object banayega memory mein
            2. Ab se jab bhi "android:" dikhe to is URL se properties lega
            3. Jaise "android:layout_width" ka matlab hai is URL se lo

    NAMESPACE KA MATLAB:
            "android:" ek shortcut hai. Poora matlab hai:
            "http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android/layout_width"
            Par hum shortcut use karte hain: "android:layout_width"
    -->

    <!--
    =====================================================================
    LINE 3: LAYOUT WIDTH
    =====================================================================
        android:layout_width="match_parent"

    EXPLANATION:
    - layout_width → Element ki width kitni hogi
    - match_parent → Jitni parent (iske andar wala container) ki width hai,
                     utni hi le lo (puri screen width)

    DRYRUN: Jab Android ye property padhega:
            1. Is LinearLayout ki width set karni hai
            2. Value = "match_parent" means parent jitna wide hona hai
            3. Parent = poori screen (kyunki ye root layout hai)
            4. Internally isko -1 se replace kar dega (match_parent = -1)
            5. Jab screen render hogi, to screen ki width nikal kar yahan laga dega

    INTERNAL WORKING:
            match_parent = -1 (Android source code mein constant hai)
            Jab layout banega: width = getParent().getWidth()
    -->

    <!--
    =====================================================================
    LINE 4: LAYOUT HEIGHT
    =====================================================================
        android:layout_height="match_parent"

    EXPLANATION:
    - layout_height → Element ki height kitni hogi
    - match_parent → Parent jitni height le lo

    DRYRUN:
            1. Height set karni hai is layout ki
            2. Parent jitni height chahiye
            3. Parent = screen, to full screen height milegi
            4. Internally height = -1 (match_parent constant)
            5. Jab layout hoga: height = screen.getHeight()
    -->

    <!--
    =====================================================================
    LINE 5: ORIENTATION
    =====================================================================
        android:orientation="vertical"

    EXPLANATION:
    - orientation → Andar wale elements (children) ko kaise arrange karna hai
    - vertical → Ek ke neeche ek (jaise queue mein log)
    - horizontal → Ek ke baad ek (jaise class mein bench par)

    DRYRUN:
            1. LinearLayout ke andar jo bhi elements aayenge
            2. Unko vertically arrange karna hai (upar se neeche)
            3. Internally: orientation = 1 (vertical = 1, horizontal = 0)
            4. Jab add karoge TextView, EditText, button, sab neeche aate jayenge

    EXAMPLE: Jaise plate mein rakhna ho:
            vertical = roti, phir sabzi, phir salad (ek upar ek)
            horizontal = roti, sabzi, salad (ek saath, bagal mein)
    -->

    <!--
    =====================================================================
    LINE 6: PADDING
    =====================================================================
        android:padding="20dp"

    EXPLANATION:
    - padding → Element ke andar ki taraf kitni jagah chhodni hai
    - 20dp → 20 density-independent pixels jagah chhoro
    - dp → Density-independent Pixels (har screen par same size dikhega)

    DRYRUN:
            1. Is LinearLayout ke andar jo bhi aayega
            2. Uske chaaron taraf (upar, neeche, left, right) 20dp gap chhoro
            3. Android calculate karega: 20dp = 20 * (screen_density/160)
            4. Agar screen density 320dpi hai: 20 * 2 = 40 pixels jagah
            5. Ye jagah border aur content ke beech mein hogi

    PADDING vs MARGIN:
            Padding = andar ki jagah (kurte mein pocket andar)
            Margin = bahar ki jagah (do plates ke beech mein gap)
    -->

